de.saxsys.mvvmfx.utils.viewlist

Interface ViewListCellFactory<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Datatype which is the mapping source
    All Superinterfaces:
    javafx.util.Callback<javafx.scene.control.ListView<T>,javafx.scene.control.ListCell<T>>, ViewTupleMapper<T>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ViewListCellFactory<T>
extends javafx.util.Callback<javafx.scene.control.ListView<T>,javafx.scene.control.ListCell<T>>, ViewTupleMapper<T>
    Factory which provides the mapping between some data to a ViewTuple. You can use this, for transforming lists of technical IDs in the ViewModel to a ListView which displays View by a given ViewTuple.
    Author:
    sialcasa
